Day 43 – Road to Fluent Spanish Summary
Today focused heavily on review and reinforcement of foundational travel and conversational Spanish phrases before beginning a fresh weekly phrase set tomorrow. The session began with Duolingo vocabulary and conversational phrase practice, including several new adjectives and descriptive phrases such as “tranquila,” “comida saludable,” “los invitados,” and “están enamorados.” Additional Memrise review focused on past tense vocabulary and directional/location terms including “el norte,” “el sur,” and “el oeste,” as well as time-based phrases like “durante dos meses” and “la última vez.”

Weekly key conversational travel phrases received a final comprehensive review before transitioning to a new set tomorrow. These included:

¿Dónde está la puerta de embarque?
¿A qué hora sale el vuelo?
Tengo una reservación a nombre de Campbell Quire
¿Qué me recomiendas del menú?
La cuenta por favor
Es mi primera vez aquí
Estoy de visita, soy de Kentucky
Hay muchas opciones
Quiero comer algo diferente
Voy a pedir el mofongo
